SIMPLE: macrocephalous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: macrocephalous
<hw>mac`ro*ceph"a*lous</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Macro</ets> + Gr. <grk>kefalh`</grk> the head.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to macrocephaly; having an unusually
large head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the cotyledons of a
dicotyledonous embryo confluent, and forming a large mass compared with
the rest of the body.</def> <rj><au>Henslow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>macrocephaly</ent>⟦br⟧
